<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10022697284967></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10022697284967><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2592&mid=10022697284967>RE:</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2592&mid=10022697284967#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16223><span id= >Kawai</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 4:15 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This bag is very useful for monks. I recently acquired one, by swapping it for a tink bag with the Paladin that won it.<br><br>He went away with a wt1.0 100% reduction 10 slot bag and I went away with a wt0.4 100% reduction 10 slot bag..so two people were happy rather than just one, which was cool.<br><br>I sent a /tell to the winner the second he was announced, offering the tink. So to you monks out there, you might want to do this if you have a tink and the non-monk winner is a reasonable sort, or you might want to establish that this should only be lottoed to monks... up to you.<br><br>Its strange to say but, I probably would have not ended up with this bag if only monks had rolled on it, seeing as there were 5 on the raid.<br><br>Regarding monk weight.. depending on your level, you lose progressively more AC for going overweight. My advice is to settle on a maximum weight/AC loss that your are comfortable with (as your worse case scenario) and try to keep a few pounds under that. I like to stick around 16/17 pounds, which means that I can loot an average nights worth of plat without breaking into 19.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
