<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100724493044975></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100724493044975><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2592&mid=100724493044975>RE:</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2592&mid=100724493044975#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93114><span id=Scholar>Navarra</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 1st 5:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As anybody will find a 100% WR bag useful, I would not call this "a monk item". If monks always want to be 100% WR on their bags, ask a nice shaman (lvl 5 gets the spell, I believe) to summon you a bunch of bags at the beginning of your EQ session - and you'll be able to carry whatever you want, just don't forget to empty out the bags at the end of the session, so you don't lose your good stuff! :)<br><br>Personally, I have a SK and a rogue, dark elf and wood elf respectively, and due to the weight of their armor and things like bags, would both find a bag like this amazingly useful, because right now neither of them can pick up too much loot without becoming encumbered. <br><br>This is a great bag for anybody, just hard to get.<br>&nbsp;<br>Navarra Meritage<br>Ranger of 47 seasons<br>Savage Arms<br>Seventh Hammer server</td></tr>
